      ],
      "grug_level": 5,
      "spiciness": 2
    },
    {
      "text": "Unit tests don't prevent bugs. They prevent the specific bugs you anticipated. Production finds the rest.",
      "author": "based",
      "author_slug": "based",
      "categories": [
        "engineering"
      ],
      "tags": [
        "testing",
        "reality"
      ],
      "grug_level": 4,
      "spiciness": 3,
      "id": "based-unit-tests-dont-prevent",
      "source": "Community sourced"
    },
    {
      "text": "Ship, then test. Not test, then ship. The market doesn't wait for your test suite.",
      "author": "based",
      "author_slug": "based",
      "categories": [
        "engineering",
        "shipping"
      ],
      "tags": [
        "shipping",
        "testing"
      ],
      "grug_level": 4,
      "spiciness": 3,
      "id": "based-ship-then-test-not",
      "source": "Community sourced"
    },
    {
      "text": "If your test suite takes more than 5 minutes, people won't run it. If people don't run it, it doesn't exist.",
      "author": "based",
      "author_slug": "based",
      "categories": [
        "engineering"
      ],
      "tags": [
        "testing",
        "developer-experience"
      ],
      "grug_level": 3,
      "spiciness": 2,
      "id": "based-if-your-test-suite",
      "source": "Community sourced"
    },
    {
      "text": "Every time you copy-paste code, a unit test dies.",
      "author": "based",
      "author_slug": "based",
      "categories": [
        "engineering",
        "shitpost"
      ],
      "tags": [
        "copy-paste",
        "testing"
      ],
      "grug_level": 3,
      "spiciness": 2,
      "id": "based-every-time-you-copypaste",
      "source": "Community sourced"
    },
    {
      "text": "If you can't test it, you can't ship it. If you can't ship it, you can't charge for it.",
      "author": "based",
      "author_slug": "based",
      "categories": [
        "engineering"
      ],
      "tags": [
        "testing",
        "shipping"
      ],
      "grug_level": 3,
      "spiciness": 2,
      "id": "based-if-you-cant-test",
      "source": "Community sourced"
    },
    {
      "text": "If you don't have a type system, your tests are your type system. If you have both, you're just being thorough.",
      "author": "based",
      "author_slug": "based",
      "categories": [
        "engineering"
      ],
      "tags": [
        "types",
        "testing"
      ],
      "grug_level": 3,
      "spiciness": 2,
      "id": "based-if-you-dont-have",
      "source": "Community sourced"
    },
    {
      "text": "Your test suite is your safety net. If it's full of holes, you'll fall through.",
      "author": "based",
      "author_slug": "based",
      "categories": [
        "engineering"
      ],
      "tags": [
        "testing",
        "coverage"
      ],
      "grug_level": 3,
      "spiciness": 2,
      "id": "based-your-test-suite-is",
      "source": "Community sourced"
    },
    {
      "text": "The best way to find a bug is to write a test that reproduces it. Not to stare at the code until it confesses.",
      "author": "based",
      "author_slug": "based",
      "categories": [
        "engineering"
      ],
      "tags": [
        "debugging",
        "testing"
      ],
      "grug_level": 3,
      "spiciness": 2,
      "id": "based-the-best-way-to-779",
      "source": "Community sourced"
    },
    {
      "text": "Your test suite should catch regressions. If it doesn't, it's just running code for no reason.",
      "author": "based",
      "author_slug": "based",
      "categories": [
        "engineering"
      ],
      "tags": [
        "testing",
        "regression"
      ],
      "grug_level": 3,
      "spiciness": 2,
      "id": "based-your-test-suite-should",
      "source": "Community sourced"
    },
    {
      "text": "I don't always test my code, but when I do, I do it in production.",
